content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 8203.1 - Definitions as used in this Part

State Regulations
(a) CYIMIS shall mean the Children and Youth

Interagency Management Information System. (b) Data subject shall mean a person about
whom information has been collected by a participating agency. (c) Participating agency shall mean a State
agency which supplies information concerning a data subject to the council for
inclusion in CYIMIS. (d) Individual
identifying data shall mean information concerning a data subject which reveals
the identity of the data subject. (e) Client specific data shall mean
information pertaining to one data subject. (f) Aggregate data shall mean information
summarizing the characteristics of a group of individual records from which
neither individual identifying data nor client specific data can be
ascertained. (g) Direct access
shall mean the ability to withdraw data from the CYIMIS data base through
electronic means, or to enter the secured area where CYIMIS data are stored for
the purpose of withdrawing data. (h) Encoded child data elements shall mean
the encoded last name, the last four digits of a data subject's social security
number and the participating agency client identification number. (i) Encoded last name shall mean a code
derived from a data subject's last name which is encoded by a participating
agency before being furnished to the council. (j) Participating agency client
identification number shall mean a code assigned by a participating agency to a
data subject before being furnished to the council. (k) Participating agency identification
number shall mean a code assigned by the council which identifies a
participating agency. (l) Council
internal identification number shall mean a code assigned by the council to
client-specific data. Notes
